1 Section 1. NRS 408.133 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 408.133 1. The Board shall adopt a plan for measuring the
3 performance of the Department, which must include separate sets of
4 performance measurements for each division of the Department and
5 for the Department as a whole.
6 2. The Director shall, not later than December 31 of each year:
7 (a) Prepare a report, based upon the relevant performance
8 measurements adopted pursuant to subsection 1, on the level of
9 achievement of each division of the Department and of the
10 Department as a whole during the immediately preceding fiscal
11 year. The report must include a discussion of:
12 (1) The goals and objectives of the Department, and the
13 current status of the Department in relation to meeting those goals
14 and objectives;
15 (2) Any applicable directives from the Board or Legislature
16 since the most recent report prepared pursuant to this section;
17 (3) The scheduling, scope, cost and progress of any current
18 or proposed highway projects [;] , including, without limitation, the
19 progress of any current or proposed project identified in the
20 inventory of connectivity pursuant to NRS 408.661 and the need
21 for any such project;
22 (4) The sources, amount and expenditure of any funding
23 received during the immediately preceding fiscal year;
24 (5) The rationale used to establish priorities for the
25 completion of highway projects; and
26 (6) Any recommendations for amendments to the plan
27 adopted pursuant to subsection 1.
28 (b) Submit the report to:
29 (1) The Board; and
30 (2) The Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau for
31 transmittal to the Interim Finance Committee.
